#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an8.7"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.7:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.7:0.2"
msgid "1. Mettāvagga "
msgstr "1. Love "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an8.7:0.3"
msgid "7. Devadattavipattisutta "
msgstr "7. Devadatta’s Failure "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an8.7:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate acirapakkante devadatte. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain, not long after Devadatta had left. "

msgctxt "an8.7:1.2"
msgid "Tatra bhagavā devadattaṃ ārabbha bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha spoke to the mendicants about Devadatta: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.7:1.3"
msgid "“sādhu, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kālena kālaṃ attavipattiṃ paccavekkhitā hoti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, it’s good for a mendicant to check their own failings from time to time. "

msgctxt "an8.7:1.4"
msgid "Sādhu, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kālena kālaṃ paravipattiṃ paccavekkhitā hoti. "
msgstr "It’s good for a mendicant to check the failings of others from time to time. "

msgctxt "an8.7:1.5"
msgid "Sādhu, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kālena kālaṃ attasampattiṃ paccavekkhitā hoti. "
msgstr "It’s good for a mendicant to check their own successes from time to time. "

msgctxt "an8.7:1.6"
msgid "Sādhu, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kālena kālaṃ parasampattiṃ paccavekkhitā hoti. "
msgstr "It’s good for a mendicant to check the successes of others from time to time. "

msgctxt "an8.7:1.7"
msgid "Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, asaddhammehi abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto devadatto āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho. "
msgstr "Overcome and overwhelmed by eight things that oppose the true teaching, Devadatta is going to a place of loss, to hell, there to remain for an eon, irredeemable. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an8.7:2.1"
msgid "Katamehi aṭṭhahi? "
msgstr "What eight? "

msgctxt "an8.7:2.2"
msgid "Lābhena hi, bhikkhave, abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto devadatto āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho. "
msgstr "Overcome and overwhelmed by gain … "

msgctxt "an8.7:2.3"
msgid "Alābhena, bhikkhave … pe … "
msgstr "loss … "

msgctxt "an8.7:2.4"
msgid "yasena, bhikkhave … "
msgstr "fame … "

msgctxt "an8.7:2.5"
msgid "ayasena, bhikkhave … "
msgstr "disgrace … "

msgctxt "an8.7:2.6"
msgid "sakkārena, bhikkhave … "
msgstr "honor … "

msgctxt "an8.7:2.7"
msgid "asakkārena, bhikkhave … "
msgstr "dishonor … "

msgctxt "an8.7:2.8"
msgid "pāpicchatāya, bhikkhave … "
msgstr "wicked desires … "

msgctxt "an8.7:2.9"
msgid "pāpamittatāya, bhikkhave, abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto devadatto āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho. "
msgstr "bad friendship, Devadatta is going to a place of loss, to hell, there to remain for an eon, irredeemable. "

msgctxt "an8.7:2.10"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahi asaddhammehi abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto devadatto āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho. "
msgstr "Overcome and overwhelmed by these eight things that oppose the true teaching, Devadatta is going to a place of loss, to hell, there to remain for an eon, irredeemable. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.161, sc3
msgctxt "an8.7:3.1"
msgid "Sādhu, bhikkhave, bhikkhu uppannaṃ lābhaṃ abhibhuyya abhibhuyya vihareyya, "
msgstr "It’s good for a mendicant, whenever they encounter it, to overcome gain … "

msgctxt "an8.7:3.2"
msgid "uppannaṃ alābhaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "loss … "

msgctxt "an8.7:3.3"
msgid "uppannaṃ yasaṃ … "
msgstr "fame … "

msgctxt "an8.7:3.4"
msgid "uppannaṃ ayasaṃ … "
msgstr "disgrace … "

msgctxt "an8.7:3.5"
msgid "uppannaṃ sakkāraṃ … "
msgstr "honor … "

msgctxt "an8.7:3.6"
msgid "uppannaṃ asakkāraṃ … "
msgstr "dishonor … "

msgctxt "an8.7:3.7"
msgid "uppannaṃ pāpicchataṃ … "
msgstr "wicked desires … "

msgctxt "an8.7:3.8"
msgid "uppannaṃ pāpamittataṃ abhibhuyya abhibhuyya vihareyya. "
msgstr "bad friendship. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
#. VAR: Kiñca → kathañca (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an8.7:4.1"
msgid "Kiñca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca uppannaṃ lābhaṃ abhibhuyya abhibhuyya vihareyya, "
msgstr "What advantage does a mendicant gain by overcoming these eight things? "

